39    /**
40    * Scope contains information about a variable scope in JavaScript.
41    * Scopes can be nested, a scope points back to its parent scope.
42    * A Scope contains information about variables defined in that scope.
43    * <p>
44    * A Scope is also used as a lattice element for flow-sensitive type inference.
45    * As a lattice element, a Scope is viewed as a map from names to types. A name
46    * not in the map is considered to have the bottom type. The join of two maps m1
47    * and m2 is the map of the union of names with {@link JSType#getLeastSupertype}
48    * to meet the m1 type and m2 type.
49    *
50    * @see NodeTraversal
51    * @see DataFlowAnalysis
52    *
53    */
